            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine omnipotentis Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina ordinante clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Morem sequimur piorum predecessorum
                        nostrorum si ecclesiis Dei et eius sacerdotibus augmentum et utilitates
                        conferimus. Idcirco omnium fidelium sancte Dei Ecclesie nostrorumque
                        presentium scilicet ac futurorum noverit solertia, quia ob
                            imprecationem<persName key="#Intercessory #Queen #marriage"
                            ref="#people/155">
                            <rs key="#Intercessory #Queen #marriage">Berctilla dilecte coniugis et
                                consortis regni nostri</rs></persName> concedimus <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Relics" ref="#juridical_persons/101"><rs key="#Churches"
                                >sancte Cenedensi ecclesie</rs>
                        </orgName>ubi <rs key="#Relics">corpus beati Ticiani</rs> confessoris
                        humatum quiescit unum <geogName
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Fluvial_transport #Markets #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#estates/507"><placeName
                                key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#places/907"><rs
                                    key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Fluvial_transport"
                                    >portum in Liquentia quod Septimum</rs></placeName></geogName>
                        dicitur et sicut predictum flumen oritur et defluit usque in mare de ambabus
                        partibus ripe per quindecim pedes <rs
                            key="#Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">palisficturam,
                            ripaticum, toloneum</rs>, <rs key="#Markets">mercatum</rs> iuris regni
                        nostri seu quicquid ad eundem portum vel in eisdem finibus pertinere
                        dignoscitur, nec non et <geogName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/506"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/908"><rs
                                    key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >silvam de Gaio et Girano</rs> cum <rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >corte </rs></placeName></geogName>et cum omni integritate sua
                        in longitudine et latitudine, prout hactenus nostre pertinuit parti per hoc
                        nostre auctoritatis preceptum de nostro iure in ius et potestatem
                        proprietariam prelibate sancte Cenedensis ecclesie, ubi presenti tempore
                            <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/620"><rs key="#Bishops">Ricpaldus
                                venerabilis episcopus</rs></persName> sacerdotii iura gubernat, ex
                        integro conferimus et largimur ad habendum, tenendum, possidendum seu
                        quicquid voluerit faciendum, remota totius potestatis inquietudine vel
                        minoratione. Si quis igitur contra hoc nostre donationis preceptum ausu
                        nefario insurgere temptaverit et a potestate iam dicte ecclesie subtrahere
                        quesierit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras
                            mille</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">[camere] palatii
                            nostri</rs> et medietatem prenominate <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie
                        </rs>eiusque rectoribus. Quod ut verius ab omnibus credatur diligen[tiusque
                        ab omn]ibus observetur, manu propria roboratum de anulo nostri nominis
                        assignari subter precepimus. [Signum d]omni Bere[ngarii] (M) serenissimi
                        regis. <persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/619">Ambrosius <rs
                                key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs></persName> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor" ref="#people/216">Ardingi <rs
                                key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii </rs></persName>recognovi [et
                        subscripsi] Data non. aug., anno dominice incarnationis .DCCCCXCVI., regni
                        domni Berengarii piissimi regis .XXI., indictione .XI. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/909">Summo lacu</placeName>. in Dei nomine feliciter. </ab>
